{"priority": "major", "kind": "enhancement", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo-release.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo-release"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{95a21594-633d-4752-b9d6-5be95d20150c}ts=default"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo-release", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo-release", "uuid": "{95a21594-633d-4752-b9d6-5be95d20150c}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo-release/issues/32/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo-release/issues/32.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo-release/issues/32/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo-release/issues/32/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo-release/issues/32/use-gnuinstalldirs-to-provide-file"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo-release/issues/32/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/109284c8b83411dbc7492138f6167e9ed=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsJR-5.png"}}, "nickname": "Jose Luis Rivero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:155a32e2-420c-4d50-98e0-0e722f63f906"}, "title": "Use GNUInstallDirs to provide file deployment destinations", "component": null, "votes": 0, "watches": 1, "content": {"raw": "This issue and proposed solution was recommended by @thomas_moulard via mail:\r\n\r\nGazebo makes the assumption that all distributions follow the FHS (Filesystem Hiearchy\r\nStandard). Unfortunately this is not the case. Therefore, a solution could be to use the GNUInstallDirs.cmake module to allow deployment customization.\r\n\r\nFor instance, how this was done for [console_bridge](https://github.com/thomas-moulard/console_bridge/commit/3830f26069d7daac82599530e8d0d6c745b82d13)", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>This issue and proposed solution was recommended by @thomas_moulard via mail:</p>\n<p>Gazebo makes the assumption that all distributions follow the FHS (Filesystem Hiearchy\nStandard). Unfortunately this is not the case. Therefore, a solution could be to use the GNUInstallDirs.cmake module to allow deployment customization.</p>\n<p>For instance, how this was done for <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://github.com/thomas-moulard/console_bridge/commit/3830f26069d7daac82599530e8d0d6c745b82d13\" rel=\"nofollow\">console_bridge</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/109284c8b83411dbc7492138f6167e9ed=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsJR-5.png"}}, "nickname": "Jose Luis Rivero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:155a32e2-420c-4d50-98e0-0e722f63f906"}, "state": "resolved", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2013-07-14T19:10:27.573805+00:00", "milestone": {"name": "debian-requirement", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo-release/milestones/71195.json"}}}, "updated_on": "2013-08-26T16:11:19.413656+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 32}